Rating: 3
My dad and husband absolutely loved this. I thought it was pretty good, but a little too sweet for my taste. Next time I would reduce the molasses. I only used 1/3 cup cider vinegar, as suggested by other reviewers, and that seemed to work well. I did not have to remove the lid at the end to reduce the sauce, as some other reviewers did. There was exactly the right amount of sauce in mine. I also added about 1/2 a head of chopped garlic and used garbanzos, black beans, and kidney beans. Garnished with fresh basil. Next time will add more greens at the end, ideally cilantro, but garlic chives would work nicely too.

