I made this the other night in the crock pot - just too hot to use the oven these days. I cooked the bacon and poured off all the drippings, then sauteed the onion and added it to the crock pot. It turned out nicely. I cut the vinegar to 1/3 cup but I still think it was a little too much, it's quite tangy. Or perhaps it's because I used Heinz chili sauce instead of ketchup (found out at the last minute that I didn't have any). Great for a weeknight BBQ or for camping.

Rating: 3
I followed the advice of the others who recommended reducing the vinegar to 2TB, and not using all the bacon drippings to sautee the onions. Next time I might try adding a little more vinegar. I used a Pyrex casserole w/lid and it baked out great---did not need more water. To make things easier for me, I mixed everything (except bacon)together in the casserole dish the night before and held it in the refrig. I baked the casserole out an hour before our picnic supper. Definitely a time saver. A very tasty dish!

